How to set an alias permanently
First step, make the following statement with the desired alias and the function you want to use the alias for:
desired_alias='function_you_want_to_replace'

WARNING: it is really important you have no spaces around the "="!

Second step, add the previous command to the following file:
nano ~/.bashrc -----> paste ALIAS + alias command at the very end of this file. YOU MUST ADD THE WORD alias BEFORE THE COMMAND LKE THISs:

alias desired_alias='function_you_want_to_replace'

Third step,  run the followind command:
source ~/.bashrc

Restart your machine and now your new alias can be used for the function you wanted to replace.
